{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":791,"text":"We are going to take a quick voyage"},{"time":3190,"text":"over the cognitive history of the 20th century,"},{"time":6697,"text":"because during that century,"},{"time":8486,"text":"our minds have altered dramatically."},{"time":11400,"text":"As you all know, the cars that people drove in 1900"},{"time":14724,"text":"have altered because the roads are better"},{"time":16798,"text":"and because of technology."},{"time":19153,"text":"And our minds have altered, too."},{"time":21122,"text":"We've gone from people who confronted a concrete world"},{"time":25066,"text":"and analyzed that world primarily in terms"},{"time":28465,"text":"of how much it would benefit them"},{"time":30698,"text":"to people who confront a very complex world,"},{"time":35290,"text":"and it's a world where we've had to develop"},{"time":37499,"text":"new mental habits, new habits of mind."},{"time":40994,"text":"And these include things like"},{"time":42991,"text":"clothing that concrete world with classification,"},{"time":47005,"text":"introducing abstractions that we try to make"},{"time":49927,"text":"logically consistent,"},{"time":52123,"text":"and also taking the hypothetical seriously,"},{"time":54953,"text":"that is, wondering about what might have been"},{"time":57203,"text":"rather than what is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":59595,"text":"Now, this dramatic change was drawn to my attention"},{"time":63147,"text":"through massive I.Q. gains over time,"},{"time":66907,"text":"and these have been truly massive."},{"time":69276,"text":"That is, we don't just get a few more questions right"},{"time":73687,"text":"on I.Q. tests."},{"time":75160,"text":"We get far more questions right on I.Q. tests"},{"time":78619,"text":"than each succeeding generation"},{"time":80867,"text":"back to the time that they were invented."},{"time":83777,"text":"Indeed, if you score the people a century ago"},{"time":87075,"text":"against modern norms,"},{"time":88623,"text":"they would have an average I.Q. of 70."},{"time":91994,"text":"If you score us against their norms,"},{"time":94719,"text":"we would have an average I.Q. of 130."},{"time":98318,"text":"Now this has raised all sorts of questions."},{"time":101675,"text":"Were our immediate ancestors"},{"time":103580,"text":"on the verge of mental retardation?"},{"time":106815,"text":"Because 70 is normally the score for mental retardation."},{"time":110890,"text":"Or are we on the verge of all being gifted?"},{"time":113922,"text":"Because 130 is the cutting line for giftedness."}]},{"cues":[{"time":118158,"text":"Now I'm going to try and argue for a third alternative"},{"time":121278,"text":"that's much more illuminating than either of those,"},{"time":125331,"text":"and to put this into perspective,"},{"time":127953,"text":"let's imagine that a Martian came down to Earth"},{"time":130858,"text":"and found a ruined civilization."},{"time":133693,"text":"And this Martian was an archaeologist,"},{"time":136100,"text":"and they found scores, target scores,"},{"time":138987,"text":"that people had used for shooting."},{"time":141910,"text":"And first they looked at 1865,"},{"time":144413,"text":"and they found that in a minute,"},{"time":146484,"text":"people had only put one bullet in the bullseye."},{"time":150193,"text":"And then they found, in 1898,"},{"time":152510,"text":"that they'd put about five bullets in the bullseye in a minute."},{"time":156294,"text":"And then about 1918 they put a hundred bullets in the bullseye."},{"time":161521,"text":"And initially, that archaeologist would be baffled."},{"time":165376,"text":"They would say, look, these tests were designed"},{"time":167973,"text":"to find out how much people were steady of hand,"},{"time":171571,"text":"how keen their eyesight was,"},{"time":174346,"text":"whether they had control of their weapon."},{"time":176684,"text":"How could these performances have escalated"},{"time":179705,"text":"to this enormous degree?"},{"time":181887,"text":"Well we now know, of course, the answer."},{"time":184162,"text":"If that Martian looked at battlefields,"},{"time":186974,"text":"they would find that people had only muskets"},{"time":189798,"text":"at the time of the Civil War"},{"time":191862,"text":"and that they had repeating rifles"},{"time":193669,"text":"at the time of the Spanish-American War,"},{"time":196854,"text":"and then they had machine guns"},{"time":198590,"text":"by the time of World War I."},{"time":201405,"text":"And, in other words, it was the equipment"},{"time":203956,"text":"that was in the hands of the average soldier"},{"time":206123,"text":"that was responsible, not greater keenness of eye"},{"time":209186,"text":"or steadiness of hand."}]},{"cues":[{"time":211359,"text":"Now what we have to imagine is the mental artillery"},{"time":214679,"text":"that we have picked up over those hundred years,"},{"time":218172,"text":"and I think again that another thinker will help us here,"},{"time":222235,"text":"and that's Luria."},{"time":224370,"text":"Luria looked at people"},{"time":226514,"text":"just before they entered the scientific age,"},{"time":230167,"text":"and he found that these people"},{"time":232164,"text":"were resistant to classifying the concrete world."},{"time":235821,"text":"They wanted to break it up"},{"time":236875,"text":"into little bits that they could use."},{"time":239465,"text":"He found that they were resistant"},{"time":241755,"text":"to deducing the hypothetical,"},{"time":245256,"text":"to speculating about what might be,"},{"time":247933,"text":"and he found finally that they didn't deal well"},{"time":250570,"text":"with abstractions or using logic on those abstractions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":254967,"text":"Now let me give you a sample of some of his interviews."},{"time":258107,"text":"He talked to the head man of a person"},{"time":260473,"text":"in rural Russia."},{"time":262305,"text":"They'd only had, as people had in 1900,"},{"time":264779,"text":"about four years of schooling."},{"time":266960,"text":"And he asked that particular person,"},{"time":269320,"text":"what do crows and fish have in common?"},{"time":272790,"text":"And the fellow said, \"Absolutely nothing."},{"time":275857,"text":"You know, I can eat a fish. I can't eat a crow."},{"time":278850,"text":"A crow can peck at a fish."},{"time":281176,"text":"A fish can't do anything to a crow.\""},{"time":284027,"text":"And Luria said, \"But aren't they both animals?\""},{"time":287253,"text":"And he said, \"Of course not."},{"time":288663,"text":"One's a fish."},{"time":290650,"text":"The other is a bird.\""},{"time":292422,"text":"And he was interested, effectively,"},{"time":294444,"text":"in what he could do with those concrete objects."}]},{"cues":[{"time":298112,"text":"And then Luria went to another person,"},{"time":300990,"text":"and he said to them,"},{"time":303173,"text":"\"There are no camels in Germany."},{"time":305869,"text":"Hamburg is a city in Germany."},{"time":308280,"text":"Are there camels in Hamburg?\""},{"time":310823,"text":"And the fellow said,"},{"time":311714,"text":"\"Well, if it's large enough, there ought to be camels there.\""},{"time":315933,"text":"And Luria said, \"But what do my words imply?\""},{"time":319827,"text":"And he said, \"Well, maybe it's a small village,"},{"time":322104,"text":"and there's no room for camels.\""},{"time":324673,"text":"In other words, he was unwilling to treat this"},{"time":326936,"text":"as anything but a concrete problem,"},{"time":329733,"text":"and he was used to camels being in villages,"},{"time":332291,"text":"and he was quite unable to use the hypothetical,"},{"time":336224,"text":"to ask himself what if there were no camels in Germany."}]},{"cues":[{"time":341131,"text":"A third interview was conducted"},{"time":343944,"text":"with someone about the North Pole."},{"time":346928,"text":"And Luria said, \"At the North Pole, there is always snow."},{"time":351033,"text":"Wherever there is always snow, the bears are white."},{"time":354988,"text":"What color are the bears at the North Pole?\""},{"time":358267,"text":"And the response was, \"Such a thing"},{"time":360669,"text":"is to be settled by testimony."},{"time":362979,"text":"If a wise person came from the North Pole"},{"time":365803,"text":"and told me the bears were white,"},{"time":367654,"text":"I might believe him,"},{"time":369133,"text":"but every bear that I have seen is a brown bear.\""},{"time":373338,"text":"Now you see again, this person has rejected"},{"time":376322,"text":"going beyond the concrete world"},{"time":378517,"text":"and analyzing it through everyday experience,"},{"time":381690,"text":"and it was important to that person"},{"time":383556,"text":"what color bears were --"},{"time":385118,"text":"that is, they had to hunt bears."},{"time":387399,"text":"They weren't willing to engage in this."},{"time":389808,"text":"One of them said to Luria,"},{"time":391645,"text":"\"How can we solve things that aren't real problems?"},{"time":395145,"text":"None of these problems are real."},{"time":397036,"text":"How can we address them?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":399679,"text":"Now, these three categories --"},{"time":403224,"text":"classification,"},{"time":404715,"text":"using logic on abstractions,"},{"time":406856,"text":"taking the hypothetical seriously --"},{"time":409625,"text":"how much difference do they make in the real world"},{"time":412063,"text":"beyond the testing room?"},{"time":413956,"text":"And let me give you a few illustrations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":416926,"text":"First, almost all of us today get a high school diploma."},{"time":420315,"text":"That is, we've gone from four to eight years of education"},{"time":423712,"text":"to 12 years of formal education,"},{"time":426489,"text":"and 52 percent of Americans"},{"time":428390,"text":"have actually experienced some type of tertiary education."},{"time":432210,"text":"Now, not only do we have much more education,"},{"time":436242,"text":"and much of that education is scientific,"},{"time":438935,"text":"and you can't do science without classifying the world."},{"time":442945,"text":"You can't do science without proposing hypotheses."},{"time":446804,"text":"You can't do science without making it logically consistent."},{"time":450978,"text":"And even down in grade school, things have changed."},{"time":454788,"text":"In 1910, they looked at the examinations"},{"time":457722,"text":"that the state of Ohio gave to 14-year-olds,"},{"time":461542,"text":"and they found that they were all"},{"time":463148,"text":"for socially valued concrete information."},{"time":466583,"text":"They were things like,"},{"time":467914,"text":"what are the capitals of the 44 or 45 states"},{"time":470801,"text":"that existed at that time?"},{"time":473175,"text":"When they looked at the exams"},{"time":474753,"text":"that the state of Ohio gave in 1990,"},{"time":477900,"text":"they were all about abstractions."},{"time":480286,"text":"They were things like,"},{"time":481879,"text":"why is the largest city of a state rarely the capital?"},{"time":487013,"text":"And you were supposed to think, well,"},{"time":488577,"text":"the state legislature was rural-controlled,"},{"time":491791,"text":"and they hated the big city,"},{"time":493889,"text":"so rather than putting the capital in a big city,"},{"time":496482,"text":"they put it in a county seat."},{"time":497920,"text":"They put it in Albany rather than New York."},{"time":500656,"text":"They put it in Harrisburg rather than Philadelphia."},{"time":503712,"text":"And so forth."},{"time":505647,"text":"So the tenor of education has changed."},{"time":508078,"text":"We are educating people to take the hypothetical seriously,"},{"time":512112,"text":"to use abstractions, and to link them logically."}]},{"cues":[{"time":515690,"text":"What about employment?"},{"time":518071,"text":"Well, in 1900, three percent of Americans"},{"time":521971,"text":"practiced professions that were cognitively demanding."},{"time":525513,"text":"Only three percent were lawyers or doctors or teachers."},{"time":529568,"text":"Today, 35 percent of Americans"},{"time":532431,"text":"practice cognitively demanding professions,"},{"time":535750,"text":"not only to the professions proper like lawyer"},{"time":538376,"text":"or doctor or scientist or lecturer,"},{"time":540925,"text":"but many, many sub-professions"},{"time":542743,"text":"having to do with being a technician,"},{"time":544684,"text":"a computer programmer."},{"time":546709,"text":"A whole range of professions now make cognitive demands."},{"time":551033,"text":"And we can only meet the terms of employment"},{"time":553963,"text":"in the modern world by being cognitively"},{"time":556460,"text":"far more flexible."},{"time":558721,"text":"And it's not just that we have many more people"},{"time":561944,"text":"in cognitively demanding professions."},{"time":564934,"text":"The professions have been upgraded."},{"time":567337,"text":"Compare the doctor in 1900,"},{"time":569448,"text":"who really had only a few tricks up his sleeve,"},{"time":572497,"text":"with the modern general practitioner or specialist,"},{"time":575305,"text":"with years of scientific training."},{"time":577984,"text":"Compare the banker in 1900,"},{"time":580253,"text":"who really just needed a good accountant"},{"time":582666,"text":"and to know who was trustworthy in the local community"},{"time":585842,"text":"for paying back their mortgage."},{"time":588133,"text":"Well, the merchant bankers who brought the world to their knees"},{"time":591362,"text":"may have been morally remiss,"},{"time":593128,"text":"but they were cognitively very agile."},{"time":596267,"text":"They went far beyond that 1900 banker."},{"time":600878,"text":"They had to look at computer projections"},{"time":603045,"text":"for the housing market."},{"time":605045,"text":"They had to get complicated CDO-squared"},{"time":608950,"text":"in order to bundle debt together"},{"time":611400,"text":"and make debt look as if it were actually a profitable asset."},{"time":615159,"text":"They had to prepare a case to get rating agencies"},{"time":618259,"text":"to give it a AAA,"},{"time":619370,"text":"though in many cases, they had virtually bribed the rating agencies."},{"time":623604,"text":"And they also, of course, had to get people"},{"time":625633,"text":"to accept these so-called assets"},{"time":628320,"text":"and pay money for them"},{"time":629820,"text":"even though they were highly vulnerable."},{"time":632407,"text":"Or take a farmer today."},{"time":633997,"text":"I take the farm manager of today as very different"},{"time":637277,"text":"from the farmer of 1900."},{"time":639768,"text":"So it hasn't just been the spread"},{"time":641606,"text":"of cognitively demanding professions."},{"time":644797,"text":"It's also been the upgrading of tasks"},{"time":647177,"text":"like lawyer and doctor and what have you"},{"time":649744,"text":"that have made demands on our cognitive faculties."}]},{"cues":[{"time":653521,"text":"But I've talked about education and employment."},{"time":656680,"text":"Some of the habits of mind that we have developed"},{"time":660019,"text":"over the 20th century"},{"time":661626,"text":"have paid off in unexpected areas."},{"time":664221,"text":"I'm primarily a moral philosopher."},{"time":666492,"text":"I merely have a holiday in psychology,"},{"time":670180,"text":"and what interests me in general is moral debate."},{"time":674588,"text":"Now over the last century,"},{"time":677319,"text":"in developed nations like America,"},{"time":679669,"text":"moral debate has escalated"},{"time":681650,"text":"because we take the hypothetical seriously,"},{"time":684989,"text":"and we also take universals seriously"},{"time":688204,"text":"and look for logical connections."},{"time":691000,"text":"When I came home in 1955 from university"},{"time":694735,"text":"at the time of Martin Luther King,"},{"time":697042,"text":"a lot of people came home at that time"},{"time":699364,"text":"and started having arguments with their parents and grandparents."},{"time":703114,"text":"My father was born in 1885,"},{"time":706342,"text":"and he was mildly racially biased."},{"time":708905,"text":"As an Irishman, he hated the English so much"},{"time":711008,"text":"he didn't have much emotion for anyone else."},{"time":713329,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":716600,"text":"But he did have a sense that black people were inferior."},{"time":721108,"text":"And when we said to our parents and grandparents,"},{"time":723956,"text":"\"How would you feel if tomorrow morning you woke up black?\""},{"time":728449,"text":"they said that is the dumbest thing you've ever said."},{"time":732070,"text":"Who have you ever known who woke up in the morning --"},{"time":734572,"text":"(Laughter) --"},{"time":736974,"text":"that turned black?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":738204,"text":"In other words, they were fixed in the concrete"},{"time":741720,"text":"mores and attitudes they had inherited."},{"time":745233,"text":"They would not take the hypothetical seriously,"},{"time":748244,"text":"and without the hypothetical,"},{"time":749728,"text":"it's very difficult to get moral argument off the ground."},{"time":753747,"text":"You have to say, imagine you were"},{"time":756382,"text":"in Iran, and imagine that your relatives"},{"time":761967,"text":"all suffered from collateral damage"},{"time":764667,"text":"even though they had done no wrong."},{"time":766613,"text":"How would you feel about that?"},{"time":768674,"text":"And if someone of the older generation says,"},{"time":771394,"text":"well, our government takes care of us,"},{"time":773324,"text":"and it's up to their government to take care of them,"},{"time":776267,"text":"they're just not willing to take the hypothetical seriously."},{"time":780335,"text":"Or take an Islamic father whose daughter has been raped,"},{"time":783702,"text":"and he feels he's honor-bound to kill her."},{"time":786912,"text":"Well, he's treating his mores"},{"time":789272,"text":"as if they were sticks and stones and rocks that he had inherited,"},{"time":793172,"text":"and they're unmovable in any way by logic."},{"time":795817,"text":"They're just inherited mores."},{"time":798393,"text":"Today we would say something like,"},{"time":800594,"text":"well, imagine you were knocked unconscious and sodomized."},{"time":804171,"text":"Would you deserve to be killed?"},{"time":805844,"text":"And he would say, well that's not in the Koran."},{"time":808739,"text":"That's not one of the principles I've got."},{"time":812761,"text":"Well you, today, universalize your principles."},{"time":815602,"text":"You state them as abstractions and you use logic on them."},{"time":819159,"text":"If you have a principle such as,"},{"time":821432,"text":"people shouldn't suffer unless they're guilty of something,"},{"time":825078,"text":"then to exclude black people"},{"time":827174,"text":"you've got to make exceptions, don't you?"},{"time":829672,"text":"You have to say, well, blackness of skin,"},{"time":832660,"text":"you couldn't suffer just for that."},{"time":835283,"text":"It must be that blacks are somehow tainted."},{"time":838546,"text":"And then we can bring empirical evidence to bear, can't we,"},{"time":841713,"text":"and say, well how can you consider all blacks tainted"},{"time":844629,"text":"when St. Augustine was black and Thomas Sowell is black."},{"time":848423,"text":"And you can get moral argument off the ground, then,"},{"time":851848,"text":"because you're not treating moral principles as concrete entities."},{"time":856402,"text":"You're treating them as universals,"},{"time":858339,"text":"to be rendered consistent by logic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":861118,"text":"Now how did all of this arise out of I.Q. tests?"},{"time":864248,"text":"That's what initially got me going on cognitive history."},{"time":868258,"text":"If you look at the I.Q. test,"},{"time":870143,"text":"you find the gains have been greatest in certain areas."},{"time":874128,"text":"The similarities subtest of the Wechsler"},{"time":876731,"text":"is about classification,"},{"time":879000,"text":"and we have made enormous gains"},{"time":881080,"text":"on that classification subtest."},{"time":884190,"text":"There are other parts of the I.Q. test battery"},{"time":887471,"text":"that are about using logic on abstractions."},{"time":890567,"text":"Some of you may have taken Raven's Progressive Matrices,"},{"time":894041,"text":"and it's all about analogies."},{"time":896579,"text":"And in 1900, people could do simple analogies."},{"time":900435,"text":"That is, if you said to them, cats are like wildcats."},{"time":904780,"text":"What are dogs like?"},{"time":906356,"text":"They would say wolves."},{"time":908448,"text":"But by 1960, people could attack Raven's"},{"time":911992,"text":"on a much more sophisticated level."},{"time":914642,"text":"If you said, we've got two squares followed by a triangle,"},{"time":919149,"text":"what follows two circles?"},{"time":921385,"text":"They could say a semicircle."},{"time":923672,"text":"Just as a triangle is half of a square,"},{"time":925850,"text":"a semicircle is half of a circle."},{"time":928568,"text":"By 2010, college graduates, if you said"},{"time":932161,"text":"two circles followed by a semicircle,"},{"time":935396,"text":"two sixteens followed by what,"},{"time":938186,"text":"they would say eight, because eight is half of 16."},{"time":941922,"text":"That is, they had moved so far from the concrete world"},{"time":944788,"text":"that they could even ignore"},{"time":947081,"text":"the appearance of the symbols that were involved in the question."}]},{"cues":[{"time":951604,"text":"Now, I should say one thing that's very disheartening."},{"time":954768,"text":"We haven't made progress on all fronts."},{"time":957640,"text":"One of the ways in which we would like to deal"},{"time":960404,"text":"with the sophistication of the modern world"},{"time":962602,"text":"is through politics,"},{"time":964638,"text":"and sadly you can have humane moral principles,"},{"time":967973,"text":"you can classify, you can use logic on abstractions,"},{"time":972393,"text":"and if you're ignorant of history and of other countries,"},{"time":975323,"text":"you can't do politics."},{"time":977750,"text":"We've noticed, in a trend among young Americans,"},{"time":980770,"text":"that they read less history and less literature"},{"time":983645,"text":"and less material about foreign lands,"},{"time":986255,"text":"and they're essentially ahistorical."},{"time":987950,"text":"They live in the bubble of the present."},{"time":990067,"text":"They don't know the Korean War from the war in Vietnam."},{"time":992923,"text":"They don't know who was an ally of America in World War II."},{"time":997106,"text":"Think how different America would be"},{"time":999727,"text":"if every American knew that this is the fifth time"},{"time":1003323,"text":"Western armies have gone to Afghanistan to put its house in order,"},{"time":1007417,"text":"and if they had some idea of exactly what had happened"},{"time":1010781,"text":"on those four previous occasions."},{"time":1013106,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1014056,"text":"And that is, they had barely left,"},{"time":1016004,"text":"and there wasn't a trace in the sand."},{"time":1018336,"text":"Or imagine how different things would be"},{"time":1021544,"text":"if most Americans knew that we had been lied"},{"time":1024300,"text":"into four of our last six wars."},{"time":1027225,"text":"You know, the Spanish didn't sink the battleship Maine,"},{"time":1030159,"text":"the Lusitania was not an innocent vessel"},{"time":1032417,"text":"but was loaded with munitions,"},{"time":1035050,"text":"the North Vietnamese did not attack the Seventh Fleet,"},{"time":1039128,"text":"and, of course, Saddam Hussein hated al Qaeda"},{"time":1042696,"text":"and had nothing to do with it,"},{"time":1044605,"text":"and yet the administration convinced 45 percent of the people"},{"time":1048408,"text":"that they were brothers in arms,"},{"time":1049952,"text":"when he would hang one from the nearest lamppost."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1053831,"text":"But I don't want to end on a pessimistic note."},{"time":1057300,"text":"The 20th century has shown enormous cognitive reserves"},{"time":1061818,"text":"in ordinary people that we have now realized,"},{"time":1065471,"text":"and the aristocracy was convinced"},{"time":1067535,"text":"that the average person couldn't make it,"},{"time":1069714,"text":"that they could never share their mindset"},{"time":1072680,"text":"or their cognitive abilities."},{"time":1075286,"text":"Lord Curzon once said"},{"time":1077000,"text":"he saw people bathing in the North Sea,"},{"time":1079264,"text":"and he said, \"Why did no one tell me"},{"time":1080927,"text":"what white bodies the lower orders have?\""},{"time":1083903,"text":"As if they were a reptile."},{"time":1086254,"text":"Well, Dickens was right and he was wrong. [Correction: Rudyard Kipling]"},{"time":1089304,"text":"[Kipling] said, \"The colonel's lady and Judy O'Grady"},{"time":1093014,"text":"are sisters underneath the skin.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1096223,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}